images.title: Qatar
images.description:
For ten months, we lived in Qatar, in the city of Doha. You might be wondering... Qa-what?

Qatar. Size of Rhode Island. Has more oil and natural gas reserves than the entire United States.

So. Qatar wants to modernize its school systems, so they imported scads of education experts, including Sarah.

images.title: Ecuador
images.description:
Otovalo

Imbabura volcano presides over Otovalo, a town near Quito that has a reputation as one of the best handicraft markets in South America.

We visited in September 2009, and we did all of our Christmas shopping.

images.title: Ecuador
images.description:
Quito

August-September 2009

We lived in Quito while we studied Spanish. We took an intensive course involving 4 hours of one-on-one instruction, 5 days a week. After two months, could we speak Spanish? Eh. Más o menos.

images.title: Ecuador
images.description:
We spent 4 months being managers at the Black Sheep Inn, an eco-lodge way up in the Andes mountains.

The black sheep pictured here is Dumbo, who is no longer with us. You can even see the tether line that was later to tangle and choke him. Poor bugger.

images.title: Ecuador

Cuyabeno River.

We spent four nights in the Amazon jungle. The Cuyabeno is a tributary of the Amazon.

Here you can see Sarah's vicious barracuda catch.

images.title: Aurangabad
images.description:
Aurangabad

Ajanta and Ellora caves

November, 2019


For Thanksgiving 2019, we traveled to Aurangabad.


It's a small city near Mumbai, the site of a bunch of historical ruins.  


The Ajanta Caves and the Ellora Caves are the headliner attractions.  But there's an impressive medieval fort nearby, and another Taj Mahal too.
